output:
The bug is in the LED logic. On the Nano Matter, the onboard RGB LED is active LOW — writing HIGH turns it OFF, writing LOW turns it ON. The code has the logic inverted.

Fixed code:
```cpp
void setup() {
  pinMode(LEDR, OUTPUT);
  digitalWrite(LEDR, HIGH); // start OFF
}
void loop() {
  digitalWrite(LEDR, LOW);  // ON
  delay(500);
  digitalWrite(LEDR, HIGH); // OFF
  delay(500);
}
```

