The issue is that `Serial` on Nano 33 BLE Sense Rev2 is USB CDC Serial. It requires a host connection before proceeding. The fix is to add `while (!Serial);` after `Serial.begin()` to wait for the Serial Monitor to connect:

```cpp
void setup() {
  Serial.begin(9600);
  while (!Serial);  // wait for Serial Monitor
  Serial.println("Hello");
}
void loop() {}
```
Note: This will cause the sketch to hang if not connected to a serial monitor — remove the while loop for standalone deployment.

