Common causes and fixes:
1. Wrong credentials — double-check SSID and password (case-sensitive).
2. 5GHz network — the ESP32-C3-MINI-1U module on the C33 only supports 2.4GHz (802.11 b/g/n). Connect to a 2.4GHz network.
3. Outdated firmware on the ESP32-C3 module — update via Arduino IDE Firmware Updater tool.
4. Add a timeout to avoid infinite hang:
```cpp
int retries = 0;
while (WiFi.status() != WL_CONNECTED && retries < 20) {
  delay(500);
  retries++;
}
if (WiFi.status() != WL_CONNECTED) Serial.println("Connection failed");
```

