Two likely causes:

1. Delay too short. The MH-Z19B needs ~100ms to respond after the command is sent, not 50ms. Increase delay(50) to delay(100).

2. No preheat time. The sensor needs 3 minutes of warm-up after power-on. Add delay(180000) at the end of setup(), or check for stable readings in a timer-based approach.

3. No availability check — readBytes() may read garbage if fewer than 9 bytes arrived. Fix:
