**Three likely causes for all-zero readings:**

**Bug 1 — MPU-6050 boots in sleep mode:**
The MPU-6050 starts in sleep mode by default. `mpu.initialize()` from the i2cdevlib MPU6050 library should wake it, but if your library version is different or initialize() fails silently, the device stays asleep and returns zeros.

**Fix — explicitly wake it:**
```cpp
void setup() {
  Wire.begin();
  Wire.beginTransmission(0x68);
  Wire.write(0x6B);  // PWR_MGMT_1 register
  Wire.write(0x00);  // Write 0 to wake up
  Wire.endTransmission();
}
```

**Bug 2 — Wrong I2C address:**
If the AD0 pin on your MPU-6050 is pulled HIGH, address is 0x69, not 0x68 (default). Check your wiring.

**Bug 3 — Missing connection test:**
No verification that the MPU-6050 is actually detected before reading.

**Fixed code:**
```cpp
void setup() {
  Serial.begin(115200);
  Wire.begin();
  mpu.initialize();

  // Wake up explicitly
  Wire.beginTransmission(0x68);
  Wire.write(0x6B);
  Wire.write(0x00);
  Wire.endTransmission();

  if (!mpu.testConnection()) {
    Serial.println("MPU6050 NOT found — check wiring");
    while (1);
  }
  Serial.println("MPU6050 OK");
}
```

