```

**Bug 2 — No integral windup limiting:**
Integral term is unbounded. If the drone is held at an angle, integral grows indefinitely. When released, it overcorrects violently.

**Fix — add anti-windup clamp:**
```c
if (integral > 400.0f) integral = 400.0f;
if (integral < -400.0f) integral = -400.0f;
```

**Bug 3 — Ki=0.8 is extremely high:**
For a roll PID, Ki of 0.8 is massive. Start at 0.01–0.05 and tune up slowly. High I on a fast axis = guaranteed oscillation.

**Fixed code:**
```c
float pid_roll(float setpoint, float current, float dt) {
  static float integral = 0;
  static float prev_error = 0;

  float error = setpoint - current;

  integral += error * dt;  // dt-scaled
  if (integral > 400.0f) integral = 400.0f;
  if (integral < -400.0f) integral = -400.0f;

  float derivative = (error - prev_error) / dt;
  prev_error = error;

  // Reduced Ki from 0.8 to 0.03
  return (2.5f * error) + (0.03f * integral) + (0.1f * derivative);
}
```

**Tuning reminder:** Kp=2.5 may also be too high depending on your frame. If oscillation persists after these fixes, halve Kp first.

