WDTCSR Register Breakdown:
┌─────┬─────┬─────┬──────┬──────┬──────┬──────┬──────┐
│WDIF │WDIE │WDP3 │ WDCE │ WDE  │ WDP2 │ WDP1 │ WDP0 │
└─────┴─────┴─────┴──────┴──────┴──────┴──────┴──────┘
  7     6     5     4      3      2      1      0

- WDIF: Watchdog Interrupt Flag (cleared by writing 1)
- WDIE: Watchdog Interrupt Enable (interrupt mode)
- WDP3:WDP0: Timeout period selection
- WDCE: Watchdog Change Enable (required to modify WDE)
- WDE:  Watchdog Enable (system reset mode)

CRITICAL RULES:
1. Never disable WDT in an ISR
2. WDCE + WDE must be set simultaneously
3. New WDTCSR value must be written within 4 cycles
4. Always use wdt_reset() in time-critical loops
5. Add wdt_disable() at startup if MCU was reset by WDT

