output:
The issue is calling `leftPixels.show()` inside the pixel-setting `for` loop. Every call to `.show()` transmits the entire pixel buffer to the LEDs at that moment — so during the loop, partial states are sent to the ring causing visible flicker as pixels update one-by-one.

Fix: move `.show()` outside the loop so all pixels are set in the buffer first, then the complete frame is sent once:

void loop() {
  for (int i = 0; i < NUMPIXELS; i++) {
    leftPixels.setPixelColor(i, leftPixels.Color(255, 0, 0));
    // Do NOT call show() here
  }
  leftPixels.show(); // Send the complete frame at once
