The problem is the missing PROGMEM keyword. A 120×60 array of 4-byte longs occupies 28,800 bytes of SRAM. Most Arduino boards (Uno, Nano) have only 2 KB of SRAM, so the global array overflows the stack/heap and the microcontroller resets or behaves erratically.

