Bug: There is no length check on enteredPassword before appending the key or updating the LCD cursor position.

If the user keeps pressing keys beyond 16 characters (the LCD column width), lcd.setCursor() will receive a column value of 16 or higher, which causes undefined behavior — typically wrapping around or writing to incorrect LCD positions, corrupting the display.

