output:
The DHT11 has a maximum sampling rate of 1 Hz (once per second), but more importantly it needs at least 1–2 seconds between stable reads to avoid returning stale or error values. Polling it every 1000 ms is at the absolute edge of its limit and can cause unreliable readings.

The recommended fix is to read the sensor much less frequently — once per minute is ideal for a room thermometer:
```cpp
unsigned long lastRead = 0;
bool firstRead = true;
int temperature = 0;

void loop() {
  unsigned long interval = firstRead ? 1000 : 60000; // 1s first read, then 60s
  if (millis() - lastRead >= interval) {
    lastRead = millis();
    firstRead = false;
    temperature = dht11.readTemperature();
    sevseg.setNumber(temperature);
  }
  sevseg.refreshDisplay();
}
```
This avoids hammering the sensor while still showing a value within 1 second of boot.

