There are two issues:

1. Missing debounce check: Without the millis() - lastDebounceTime > debounceDelay guard, every bounce of the button triggers a toggle, causing the mode to flip back and forth rapidly so it appears unchanged.

2. Toggling with ! operator on a byte: microphone = !microphone works if microphone is strictly 0 or 1, but if EEPROM ever stores a corrupt value (e.g., 2), !microphone still evaluates to 0 and the toggle is lost. Explicit assignment is safer.

Fix:
void micChange() {
  int reading = digitalRead(micPIN);
  if (reading == HIGH && previousState == LOW && millis() - lastDebounceTime > debounceDelay) {
    microphone = (microphone == 1) ? 0 : 1; // explicit toggle
    showSettings(4, true);
    saveConfig();
    lastDebounceTime = millis();
  }
  previousState = reading;
}

Also remember to re-initialize the ADC (ADCSRA/ADMUX) after switching to audio-in mode if the sketch was started in mic mode.

