Two bugs:
1. Missing Content-Type header: HTTP POST requires a Content-Type header to tell the server how to parse the body. Without it, the server may reject or ignore the POST body.
Add: client.print("Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded\r\n");

2. Missing header terminator: HTTP headers must be terminated by an empty line (\r\n\r\n) before the body. The code jumps directly to the data without the blank line separator.
Add: client.print("\r\n"); BEFORE printing data.

Also, the API key is missing from the POST body. For ThingSpeak: data should be "api_key=YOUR_KEY&field1=25.3"

