This is a null pointer dereference. `ptr` is declared as `String*` and initialized to `nullptr`. Calling `ptr->length()` attempts to dereference a null pointer, which triggers a LoadProhibited exception on the ESP32 (trying to read from address 0x0).

The 'Guru Meditation Error: Core 1 panic'ed (LoadProhibited)' is the ESP32's way of reporting an illegal memory access.

Fix:
```cpp
String myString = "Hello";
void setup() {
  Serial.begin(115200);
  Serial.println(myString.length());  // safe
}
```

Or, if you need a pointer:
```cpp
String* ptr = new String("Hello");
void setup() {
  Serial.begin(115200);
  if (ptr != nullptr) {
    Serial.println(ptr->length());
  }
}
```

Always check for nullptr before dereferencing pointers. On ESP32 with limited RAM, also be cautious of `new` failing to allocate — it returns nullptr on allocation failure.

