output:
The stack overflow is caused by allocating a large local array (8192 bytes) inside a task that was created with only 1024 bytes of stack.

Each FreeRTOS task has its own dedicated stack. The `stackDepth` parameter in `xTaskCreate()` (or `xTaskCreatePinnedToCore()`) specifies stack size in BYTES (not words, unlike some other RTOS).

Fix — increase the stack size to accommodate the buffer plus function call overhead:
```cpp
void myTask(void* param) {
  char buffer[8192];
  sprintf(buffer, "Hello World");
  Serial.println(buffer);
  vTaskDelete(NULL);
}

void setup() {
  Serial.begin(115200);
  // Stack must be > buffer size + overhead (at least 10240 here)
  xTaskCreate(myTask, "MyTask", 10240, NULL, 1, NULL);
}
```

Tip: use `uxTaskGetStackHighWaterMark(NULL)` inside a task to measure minimum free stack at runtime, helping you tune the stack size to the minimum safe value.

