The code causes a **Task Watchdog Timer (TWDT) reset** because the infinite `while(true)` loop inside `loop()` never yields control back to the FreeRTOS scheduler, starving the idle task that resets the watchdog.

**Why it happens:** ESP32 uses FreeRTOS. The watchdog expects the idle task to run periodically. A tight infinite loop in a high-priority context prevents this.

**Fix options:**

**Option 1 – Add delay/yield to feed the watchdog:**
```cpp
void loop() {
  long i = 0;
  while(true) {
    i++;
    if (i % 100000 == 0) {
      vTaskDelay(1); // yield to scheduler
      // or: delay(0); works too
    }
  }
}
```

**Option 2 – Disable TWDT (not recommended for production):**
```cpp
#include <esp_task_wdt.h>
void setup() {
  Serial.begin(115200);
  esp_task_wdt_delete(NULL); // remove current task from WDT
}
```

**Option 3 – Use a FreeRTOS task with a proper loop:**
```cpp
void countTask(void *param) {
  long i = 0;
  while(true) {
    i++;
    vTaskDelay(1); // always yield in FreeRTOS tasks
  }
}
void setup() {
  Serial.begin(115200);
  xTaskCreate(countTask, "Count", 2048, NULL, 1, NULL);
}
void loop() { delay(1000); }
```

