This is a classic ESP32 ADC2 conflict. **GPIO 25 is connected to ADC2**, which is disabled/unreliable when WiFi is active.

**Root cause:** The ESP32 WiFi stack uses ADC2 internally. When WiFi is enabled, ADC2 returns random/incorrect values or errors.

**Solution: Use ADC1 pins (GPIO 32–39)**
