ESP32 supports Bluetooth Classic Serial Port Profile (SPP), which allows it to act like a serial-over-Bluetooth device — similar to a virtual COM port.

**Note:** BT Classic is only available on original ESP32, not ESP32-S2, ESP32-C3, or ESP32-H2 (BLE only).

**Complete SPP example:**
```cpp
#include <BluetoothSerial.h>

