Issue: GPS always provides UTC time. The code correctly applies `adjustTime(offset * SECS_PER_HOUR)` to convert UTC to local time. The value used, `offset = -8`, is Pacific Standard Time (UTC-8). This logic is functionally correct as long as the offset is accurate for the current season.

However, a subtle bug exists: setTime() and adjustTime() operate on the system clock in RAM but there is no persistence. If the GPS loses fix and the sketch restarts, time resets to epoch. Also, adjustTime() with a negative offset on day boundaries can produce wrong Day/Month values if not re-read from the adjusted time correctly.

Best practice:
```cpp
tmElements_t tm;
tm.Hour = Hour; tm.Minute = Minute; tm.Second = Second;
tm.Day = Day; tm.Month = Month; tm.Year = Year - 1970;
time_t utc = makeTime(tm);
time_t local = utc + (offset * SECS_PER_HOUR);
setTime(local);
```

